Okay, pet peeve time. Kilograms are units of mass, not weight, not force, and not pressure.

If you're looking at 4000 pounds of force, the metric equivalent is about 17,800 newtons. (We can talk about significant digits another time) Pressure would be pounds per square inch, with the metric equivalent being pascals. Mike Tyson had a punch of about 1800 PSI when he was in top shape, which would be 12.4MPa

Now if the lady is punching at 4000 PSI (which seems likely from the description), then her blows would be measured at 27.6MPa and she'd end up shattering bones and probably killing people.

Is that what you meant to say?

Edit: I went ahead and corrected it. Figured it was a minor touch up for accuracy.





