Down to +3; a good time to start brainstorming.

Clearly, the precise mechanics of her enhancements don't matter here. What matters is what the enhancement has done to her, to the impoverished Chinese woman from a tiny village.

Something that might be interesting would be if she has deliberately deafened herself  so as to not be able to hear orders or trigger phrases.

 - that strikes me as somewhat off, based on what I know of Chinese culture. In fact, based on how we treat humanoid SCPs in general, her name shouldn't be included in the article at all. It'd be interesting if we can't find any evidence that her village ever existed, also. The location of the village was flooded by the Three Gorges Dam, but for all the other villages that met that fate, there's at least evidence that the village existed in the past.

Hmmm the reason we don't just anesthetize her from a distance is that, if she loses consciousness for any reason other than natural sleep, the enhancements go into defense mode.

